N.Z.’s Key Says China Has Been Buying New Zealand Bonds for ‘A Long Time’

-- B y   C h r i s   B o u r k e
-- 
2011-05-29T19:29:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-29/n-z-s-key-says-china-has-been-buying-new-zealand-bonds-for-a-long-time-.html
New Zealand Prime Minister John Key
said that  China  had been buyers of the nation’s government bonds
for “a long time now” in an interview with Television New
Zealand today. “China is the big saver around the world.
Because of its domestic inflation, it can’t bring that money
home,” Key said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
